Bugs Remaining for TestFlight

Must Fix (blocking)

  Opacity slider band-aid in place — REAL FIX NEEDED before public
    launch. The brush opacity slider previously failed to cap per-stroke
    alpha (each stamp blended at slider opacity → overlapping stamps
    accumulated → a 10% slider produced near-100% alpha within a single
    stroke). Apr 27 workaround: when stroke.settings.opacity < 1.0 the
    commit path stamps into a scratch texture at opacity = 1.0 (per-pixel
    alpha caps at 1.0 by alpha blending into an empty buffer), then
    composites scratch onto the layer at slider opacity in one pass.
    BAND-AID: the in-progress preview (renderStrokePreview) still
    accumulates each frame, so the user sees a more-opaque preview
    during drag that snaps to the capped result on touchesEnded. Real
    fix: route the preview through a parallel scratch path so what you
    see is what you commit (wet-ink preview). Eraser was deliberately
    left on the direct path; eraser's own accumulation bug needs a
    different composite (subtract scratch alpha × slider from layer
    alpha) and is deferred. Memory cost: +64 MB scratch texture
    allocated lazily on first sub-100% stroke.

  Paint bucket white outline + slow flood — premultiplied-alpha halo
    around the fill plus an unbounded CPU-side BFS flood fill. Halo
    was partially fixed Apr 15 (compositor now uses .one for source
    RGB since textures store premultiplied), still visible on device.
    A bounded BFS or a GPU compute kernel pass would help.

  Move tool UX — currently extracts a full-document rect on
    touchesBegan and shows a marquee around the whole layer. Intent:
    pick the tool, drag anywhere to reposition all pixels, no marquee.
    Code is half there; needs the marquee visual hidden and the
    "tap inside selection?" check bypassed for this tool.

  Export to Photos — MISSING. Single toolbar/gallery button: composite
    visible layers (use CanvasRenderer.compositeLayersToImage, already
    extracted via compositeLayersToTexture as of Apr 27) and call
    UIImageWriteToSavedPhotosAlbum. No App Store approval beyond the
    standard Photos permission. Hard ship blocker — this is the only
    feature gap that blocks shipping.

  Onboarding keyboard layout — reverted Apr 16 after the @FocusState +
    ScrollViewReader + .ignoresSafeArea(.keyboard) stack made the UX
    worse than the bug. Future attempts: ONE minimal change at a time;
    trust iOS defaults + scrollDismissesKeyboard already wired up; ask
    before stacking modifiers.

