Pending iPad Test Plan

When back on Paige iPad, verify in this order. If any step fails, fix
before the TestFlight cut. All steps cover changes that have already
landed but are touch- or Pencil-driven and can't be trusted from the
simulator.

1. Pencil heavy pressure across all tools — draw with Pencil pressing
   hard. Stroke must NOT vanish mid-stroke. Try brush, eraser, line,
   rectangle, circle. If anything still vanishes the 511 px shader
   clamp may need raising for M-series.

2. Large brush slow draw — set brush to size 200, draw slowly with
   Pencil. Should produce a continuous stroke (not a single starting
   stamp). Try at default zoom and at zoom 3-4×.

3. Text tool — tap canvas with text tool, type "hi", Add. Should
   appear in current brush color, no crash, no white box. Try on top
   of an existing stroke (the stroke underneath must remain visible).
   Undo should remove the text.

4. Image import — pick a photo from the library. Should land aspect-
   fit, centered, on a NEW layer. Check the layers panel. Undo should
   remove layer + image together.

5. Toolbar — open the floating toolbar. Confirm "100%" readout at the
   very top. Pinch-zoom should update it live. Rotate L/R buttons gone.
   Recenter button still there.

6. AI feedback panel — get a critique, open the panel. Should default
   to the latest entry ("N of N" in the timestamp row). Tap the
   hamburger → history menu must NOT clip off the left edge (panel
   should slide right if needed).

7. Color picker (HSB sheet) — tap the toolbar swatch. Tap each preset
   (Black, White, Gray, Red, …) and confirm the color preview at the
   top matches the preset, not a vivid hue substitute. Move the
   saturation/brightness sliders down and confirm the preview actually
   goes muted. Close and re-open the picker — sliders should reflect
   whatever you last picked, not snap back to 100%.

8. Eyedropper — paint a swatch on layer 1, add layer 2 and paint a
   different color on top. Switch to layer 1. Pick the eyedropper. Tap
   the layer-2 color: brush should change to that color (composite
   sampling). Tap empty white space: brush should change to white. Tap
   fully transparent canvas at the very edge of a stroke: brush should
   NOT silently change to transparent black.

9. Selection marquee/lasso alignment — drag a rectangle selection
   across an obvious feature (a stroke or filled shape). The marching
   ants must visually wrap that feature with no vertical offset (no
   "ants below the actual selection" gap). Tap inside the visible
   ants: drag should start (move tool / drag-to-reposition). Press
   Delete: the hole should appear exactly inside the ants, not above
   them. Repeat with the lasso tool around a tighter shape. Test in
   both portrait and landscape — the safe-area inset differs and was
   the root cause.

10. Brush opacity cap — set the brush opacity slider to 10%. Draw a
    long, looping stroke that crosses itself many times. The stroke
    must NOT exceed ~10% alpha at any pixel (overlapping passes within
    the SAME stroke do not darken). Lift, draw a second stroke on top
    at 10%: it should darken the first stroke (cross-stroke darkening
    is allowed). Confirm shape tools (line/rect/circle) at 10% also
    cap. Confirm the eraser at < 100% still erases through (eraser
    deliberately routes through the unchanged direct path). Note: the
    in-progress preview during drag will look more opaque than the
    committed result — this is the documented band-aid.


